replies.body:
This Hextech Crafting sounded really cool and fun at first ... but it's truly hollow. Sure it was awesome to get a free Blackthorn Morgana skin, but the fact I can never get key drops now and my chests are gathering dust ruins the experience, because it seems like a ploy from Riot to get people spending RP on the chests & key bundles. It feels cheap.

I get that the key drops reset every month, but that's a long freaken time. If I play and win 5+ games a day or more, why does the chances of key drops shorten? That's not healthy, and makes me lose interest in the Hextech Crafting. My time spent & effort should be what grants me key drops, not by a random drop system that gets harder overtime until 30+ wins isn't enough to get myself a key drop.

{{sticker:slayer-jinx-unamused}}

Barkhoof has the right of it. All you people complaining are going to get S on, at best, 20-30 champions. And that's generous. The rest you won't own, won't put in the effort on, or won't like the champ enough to get those other boxes over the course of a year. Do you honestly believe you can get S- on 120 someodd champions, many of which you've never played or played only a few times, in the course of 365 days?

Next thing you know, you're going to have a hard time getting S- on any new champs and the keys are going to start stacking up and you'll be the same people back here complaining that boxes are too rare/too hard to get.

{{sticker:zombie-brand-mindblown}}
